HEADWORD: Endorhizous
<hw>En`do*rhi"zous</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having the
radicle of the embryo sheathed by the cotyledon, through which the
embryo bursts in germination, as in many monocotyledonous
plants.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

